"{\"uid\": \"amny.com-news-nonprofit-seeks-support-to-build-an-olympic-facility-open-to-new-yorkers\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Tackle the city, with our help.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 31, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Manage your settings.\", \"from\": 33, \"to\": 54, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tackle the city, with our help.\", \"from\": 56, \"to\": 87, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Manage your settings.\", \"from\": 89, \"to\": 110, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For years, public pools in New York City have been a hub for the community, serving as recreational and educational institutions to thousands of New Yorkers.\", \"from\": 112, \"to\": 269, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 139, \"end\": 152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999017836719, \"rank\": 6.742175462093088e-08, \"text\": \"New York City\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As high temperatures become more common, they have also become important cooling centers.\", \"from\": 270, \"to\": 359, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Last week, New York City Mayor Eric Adams and New York City Department of Parks and Recreation Commissioner Sue Donoghueannounceda new initiative to build more public pools and improve existing infrastructure in the five boroughs.\", \"from\": 361, \"to\": 591, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Let us Swim NYC\\\" is a more than $1B investment in swimming infrastructure, the highest since the 1970s.\", \"from\": 591, \"to\": 695, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In light of this initiative, the Brooklyn nonprofit organizationInclusive Community Wellness Inc.urges New York City officials to review the proposal to bring an Olympic quality flagship facility to the city, ideally in Queens or Brooklyn.\", \"from\": 697, \"to\": 936, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 730, \"end\": 738, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brooklyn\", \"score\": 0.7367566084071067, \"rank\": 0.35730034666651855, \"text\": \"Brooklyn\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brooklyn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brooklyn\"}, {\"begin\": 800, \"end\": 813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999017836719, \"rank\": 6.742175462093088e-08, \"text\": \"New York City\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 927, \"end\": 935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brooklyn\", \"score\": 0.7367566084071067, \"rank\": 0.35730034666651855, \"text\": \"Brooklyn\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brooklyn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brooklyn\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The nonprofit focuses on promoting fitness and wellness education to underserved communities throughout the New York City metropolitan area.\", \"from\": 938, \"to\": 1078, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1046, \"end\": 1077, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_metropolitan_area\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"New York City metropolitan area\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_metropolitan_area\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_metropolitan_area\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The proposed Olympic Competition Pool would attract world-class swimming, water polo, and artistic swimming teams and competitions, elevate the city's aquatic culture, and also address our city's shortage of indoor swimming facilities,\\\" according to thepetition letterto New York City officialsIn collaboration with the city and state, this would create an opportunity for the New Yorkers that otherwise have limited access to a pool.\", \"from\": 1078, \"to\": 1513, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1350, \"end\": 1363, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999017836719, \"rank\": 6.742175462093088e-08, \"text\": \"New York City\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are not talking about putting a pool in Rockefeller Center,\\\" said Michael Randazzo, executive director of Inclusive Community Wellness.Modeled similarly toAsphalt Green, the nonprofit fitness organization with two locations in Manhattan.\", \"from\": 1513, \"to\": 1754, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1591, \"end\": 1599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randazzo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999849933, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Randazzo\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randazzo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randazzo\"}, {\"begin\": 1744, \"end\": 1753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manhattan\", \"score\": 0.8841895716918655, \"rank\": 0.13080803083581255, \"text\": \"Manhattan\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manhattan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manhattan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We would offer programs as free as possible, understanding that if you wanted a competition, there would be some fees,\\\" said Randazzo.\", \"from\": 1754, \"to\": 1889, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1880, \"end\": 1888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randazzo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999849933, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Randazzo\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randazzo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randazzo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So that you can have a competitive high school swim program or a college water polo match, we'd have to work out the model to make it sustainable,\\\" he added.Photo taken at the learn to swim program at Brooklyn 